Sliggoo

Gooey

Passive Ability

When this Pokémon is hit by an attack, there is a chance it will spread slime around itself. The slime deals damage to Pokémon, Decreases their attack speed by 50% for 2s and applies a Gooey debuff. The Gooey debuff slows Pokémon by 10% for 6s and can stack up to 4 times per Pokémon. Gooey is a debuff that is applicable to Wild Pokémon and enemy players only.

When this Pokémon enters tall grass, it continually recovers HP for up to 3s, until it leaves the tall grass, uses a move, or attacks. When this Pokémon recovers HP due to Gooey, its attack gauge is progressed towards a boosted attack. This HP recovery goes on a 12s cooldown after being triggered.

60% SpA + 6 x (Level - 1) + 120

Additional 1.2% Missing HP per tick
0% SpA + 3 x (Level - 1) + 50

Attack

Auto Attack

Becomes a boosted attack with every third attack, dealing increased damage. Hitting a Pokémon afflicted with a Gooey effect with a basic attack reduces all of this Pokémon's move cooldowns by 1.5s.

Boosted attacks spew slime and if the slime hits Pokémon from a distance, a Gooey debuff is applied to those Pokémon and slows by 50% for 0.5s. If the boosted attack is used on a Pokémon in regular attack melee range, the attack deals increased damage.

100% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 0

57% SpA + 6 x (Level - 1) + 190

Bubble

Move 1

6.00s Area

Cover itself in a bubble, granting it a shield for 3s. When the shield’s effect duration ends or if this move is used again, the bubble shield pops, dealing damage to nearby opposing Pokémon and slowing them by 30% for 2s.

128% SpA + 20 x (Level - 1) + 380

Bubble Upgrade Choices

Muddy Water

4.50s Area

Splashes muddy water around itself, dealing damage to opposing Pokémon in the area of effect and applying an effect to them that decreases the amount of damage they deal by 15% for 3s. If the user deals damage to opposing Pokémon with this move, the user’s Defense and Sp. Def are increased for 2s. If Muddy Water is used within 6 seconds, the defense bonus effect is increased in intensity. The defenses bonus effect can stack up to four times.

132% SpA + 10 x (Level - 1) + 250

0% SpA + 5 x (Level - 1) + 60

Further increases the user’s Defense and Sp. Def when this move deals damage to opposing Pokémon.

0% SpA + 8 x (Level - 1) + 90

Dragon Pulse

6.00s Area

Unleashes a shock wave in the designated direction, dealing damage to Pokémon it hits up to 4 times. If the center of the shock wave hits enemy Pokémon, it deals increased damage to them and restores the user’s HP. More HP is restored when the center of the pulse deals damage to enemy Pokémon that have a Gooey slowing effect applied to them.

The fourth tick of damage can be animation cancelled by inputs (attack or movement). It is undetermined if this is a bug or not.

68% SpA + 5 x (Level - 1) + 230

40.8% SpA + 3 x (Level - 1) + 138

10% Missing HP
0% SpA + 8 x (Level - 1) + 30

11% Missing HP
0% SpA + 8 x (Level - 1) + 30

Restores more HP if the center of the shock wave hits Pokémon, and even more on Pokémon that have a Gooey debuff applied to them.

12% Missing HP
0% SpA + 8 x (Level - 1) + 30

13% Missing HP
0% SpA + 8 x (Level - 1) + 30

Tackle

Move 2

10.00s Hindrance

Charges at a Pokémon, dealing damage and throwing it. If this move hits, the user bounces back a short distance.

80% SpA + 8 x (Level - 1) + 270

Tackle Upgrade Choices

Power Whip

7.50s Hindrance

Lashes out with its horns in the designated direction, dealing damage to Pokémon in the area of effect and slowing them by 80% for 3s, decaying by 15% every 0.5s. If this move hits distant Pokémon, those Pokémon are pulled toward Goodra.

99% SpA + 8 x (Level - 1) + 330

Also applies a Gooey effect when this move hits.

Acid Spray

7.50s Hindrance

Spits acidic fluid at target Pokémon, dealing damage to Pokémon in an area of effect centered on the target slowing them by 80% for 3s, decaying by 15% every 0.5s. If this move is used again, Goodra charges in the designated direction and deals damage to opposing Pokémon it hits. If this charge hits a Pokémon that has been marked by acidic fluid, that Pokémon is thrown for 0.75s, and damage is also dealt to nearby opposing Pokémon.

46% SpA + 4 x (Level - 1) + 150

46% SpA + 4 x (Level - 1) + 150

Also applies a Gooey effect to opposing Pokémon that receive damage from either the acidic fluid or the charge.

Right as Rain

Unite Move

89s 80000 Buff

Unlocks at level 9

Causes rain to fall around the user, gradually restoring the user’s HP over 6s. While this move is active, all of the user’s basic attacks become boosted attacks.

Unite Buffs (6s duration):

40% Max HP Shield, 50% Movement Speed
